olive oil
1 carrot
1 bag green beans
1 packet couscous
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
½ packet Currants
¾ cup boiling water
1 packet pork mince
1 packet tomato paste
½ cup water
1 bag salad leaves
½ lime
1 packet Moroccan Curry Paste
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Boil the kettle. Grate carrot. Trim green beans and slice into thirds.
• Place couscous, chicken-style stock powder and currants (see ingredients) in a medium bowl.
• Add the boiling water (3/4 cup for 2 people / 1 1/2 cups for 4 people) and stir to combine. Immediately cover with a plate and leave for 5 minutes.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. • When oil is hot, cook pork mince, carrot and green beans, breaking mince up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-6 minutes.
• Add Moroccan curry paste and tomato paste and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the water and cook until slightly thickened, 2-3 minutes. Season to taste.

• While pork is cooking, fluff up couscous with a fork.
• Add salad leaves. Stir to combine and season to taste.

• Slice lime into wedges.
• Divide currant couscous between bowls. Top with Moroccan-style pork and
green beans.
• Serve with Greek-style yoghurt and lime wedges.